{{Quote|Aleema! What's the ''meaning'' of this? Is this some disgusting ''joke?''|Magda Keto, during her daughter and nephew's coup|<ref name="darklords1" />}}
'''Magda Keto''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] who ruled as [[Queen Mother]] of the [[Empress Teta system/Legends|Empress Teta system]] with her brother, [[Lord/Legends|Lord]] [[Keto]], in the [[Standard year/Legends|years]] leading up to the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]]. Keto had a daughter named [[Aleema Keto]] who, along with Lord Keto's son [[Satal Keto/Legends|Satal]], was the heir to the [[Tetan monarchy/Legends|Tetan throne]]. The Ketos were forced to share their dominion over the [[Star system/Legends|system]] with the commercial interests that controlled [[Carbonite/Legends|carbonite]] [[Mining/Legends|mines]] in the Empress Teta system. Eventually, Satal and Aleema Keto, filled with anger and resentment and possessing much free time, learned the secrets of [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] [[Sith sorcery/Legends|Sith magic]] and formed an organization known as the [[Krath/Legends|Krath]], determined to wrest control of the system from their parents. The Krath [[Political uprising of the Empress Teta system|struck]] while Magda Keto and her brother were on an inspection tour of one of the [[Orbit/Legends|orbiting]] [[Tetan carbonite smelter]]s over the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Empress Teta/Legends|Empress Teta]]. Keto and her brother were caught by surprise, as Satal and Aleema used Sith magic to overpower their [[Royal Protector|protectors]]. Magda and Lord Keto were then [[Carbon-freezing/Legends|frozen]] in carbonite by Satal and Aleema, [[Death/Legends|killing]] them; Satal and Aleema hung the former rulers as decorations in the [[Iron Citadel/Legends|Iron Citadel]], their former palace&mdash;and the Krath's new headquarters.

==Biography==
{{Quote|Its nothing, mother, really. Korus just has a little ''indigestion''.|Aleema Keto to Magda Keto|<ref name="darklords1" />}}
A [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]],<ref name="darklords1" /> [[Queen Mother]]<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|275|Magda}}</ref> Magda Keto was, along with her brother, [[Lord/Legends|Lord]] [[Keto]], the ruler of the [[Empress Teta system/Legends|Empress Teta system]] around [[4000 BBY/Legends|four thousand years before]] the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. Keto and her brother were descendants of [[Empress/Legends|Empress]] [[Teta/Legends|Teta]], the famous woman warrior who [[Unification Wars (Koros)/Legends|unified]] the seven [[Planet/Legends|worlds]] of the then-Koros [[Star system/Legends|system]] a [[5000 BBY/Legends|thousand years previous]]. The Empress Teta system was a major source of raw [[Carbonite/Legends|carbonite]], and the Ketos were forced to share their power with the commercial interests that ran carbonite [[Mining/Legends|mines]] in the system. Eventually, Magda had a daughter named [[Aleema Keto|Aleema]]. Along with Lord Keto's son, [[Satal Keto/Legends|Satal]], Aleema was the heir to the [[Tetan monarchy/Legends|Tetan throne]]. The younger Ketos, filled with anger and resentment toward their elders and with much free time on their hands, formed a [[darksider]] organization called the [[Krath/Legends|Krath]], and learned to wield [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] [[Sith sorcery/Legends|Sith magic]]. The Krath launched a [[Political uprising of the Empress Teta system|rebellion]]<ref name="darklords1" /> in [[3997 BBY]],<ref name="ECdate" /> while Magda and Lord Keto were on an inspection tour of an [[Orbit/Legends|orbiting]] [[Tetan carbonite smelter]] over the planet [[Empress Teta/Legends|Empress Teta]].<ref name="darklords1" />

Magda Keto and her brother met with [[Bearus]], the [[Chairman/Legends|chairman]] of the [[Carbonite Guild]]. As they exchanged pleasantries, Aleema and Satal, along with their royal tutor [[Korus]], arrived in a [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttle]]. There, Satal and Aleema revealed that they had turned Korus' tongue into an [[Adegan eel]] with Sith magic, and attacked Magda Keto, her brother, and the mining executives. Lord Keto ordered his [[Royal Protector]]s to apprehend Satal and Aleema, to Magda's horror; she was outraged that her brother would arrest their own children, but Keto responded that he had no choice. However, Aleema's Sith [[Mind trick/Legends#Illusion|illusions]] overpowered the Royal Protectors, leaving Magda Keto and her brother defenseless. They were led by Satal and Aleema toward a vat of molten carbonite, where they were [[Carbon-freezing/Legends|frozen]], [[Death/Legends|killing]] them. The frozen bodies of Magda and Lord Keto went on display as wall decorations in their former palace, the [[Iron Citadel/Legends|Iron Citadel]].<ref name="darklords1" />

==Personality and traits==
{{Quote|Lord Keto! You ''can't'' arrest our own children!|Magda Keto|<ref name="darklords1" />}}
Magda Keto was horrified by her daughter and nephew's attack on the carbonite smelter and their use of Sith magic, but still was opposed to her brother ordering the Royal Protectors to arrest them. She was overcome with fear when she saw what her daughter had done to Korus, asking if it was a disgusting joke.<ref name="darklords1" />

==Behind the scenes==
Magda Keto first appeared in [[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith|''Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi - Dark Lords of the Sith'']], a story arc of the [[Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi (comic series)|''Tales of the Jedi'']] comic book series, written by [[Kevin J. Anderson]] and [[Tom Veitch]] and released from late [[1994]] to early [[1995]]. Magda Keto made her sole appearance in the arc's [[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 1|first issue]], where she was killed;<ref name="darklords1" /> she was also indirectly mentioned in ''Dark Lords of the Sith''{{'s}} [[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 2|second]]<ref name="darklords2">[[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 2|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 2]]</ref> and [[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 3|third]] issues.<ref name="darklords3">[[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 3|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 3]]</ref> In her appearance, Keto was illustrated by [[Chris Gossett]].<ref name="darklords1" />

Although she appeared in the comic version of ''Dark Lords of the Sith'', Magda Keto was absent from the [[Tales of the Jedi: Dark Lords of the Sith (audio drama)|''Dark Lords of the Sith'' audio drama]]. In the audio version her lines were attributed to her brother, Lord Keto.<ref name="audio">[[Tales of the Jedi: Dark Lords of the Sith (audio drama)|''Tales of the Jedi: Dark Lords of the Sith'' audio drama]]</ref> Magda Keto's entry in ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' incorrectly listed Lord Keto as her [[Marriage/Legends|husband]], not her brother.<ref name="cswe">''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref>

